cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language generation and attribute control, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of adversarial loss and quantitative evaluation also suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) focus. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of image captioning datasets, indicating a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of reconstruction loss and back-translation loss suggests a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
